When it comes to powering smartphone performance, MediaTek is a sure-fire bet. MediaTek leads the market in chipset technology and is ranked 2nd globally when it comes to powering mobile phones. MediaTek’s chipsets give customers feature-rich, premium technology at prices affordable to the mass market. MediaTek powers a wide variety of smartphones across nearly all the popular global brands, but MediaTek technology is not limited to just smartphones. Twenty percent of homes around the world also use products powered by MediaTek including smart speakers, TVs and voice assistant devices. MediaTek boasts an array of chipsets which offer specialised and powerful performance. One of their most popular ranges of chipsets is the Helio family, which includes the following: The MediaTek Helio P brings high-end features to the mass market with a combination of performance and power efficiency, AI and smart imaging providing smartphone manufacturers with exciting platform options to deliver key features consumers want. The MediaTek Helio A is targeted at mid-range smartphones. The Helio A family will surprise you with great performance and impressive camera features that are a great base to create capable, accessible smartphones. These chipsets are particularly popular in developing markets – where value-for-money is king. The entire Helio family is incredibly popular and used in many great smartphones that you have probably either used or seen a friend using. MediaTek’s hardware is focused on supplying powerful user experiences across a range of important smartphone features. These include: The latest smartphone powered by MediaTek launched in South Africa is the Hisense Infinity H30. This smartphone offers fantastic value by using MediaTek hardware – which is more affordable than the alternatives – without sacrificing on quality and features smartphone users want most. The company has also recently launched its newest brand store on Takealot – meaning that their equipment is